Although I do not get the point of the two database drivers 100%, you could wright your own custom class loader - based on `URLClassLoader`: 

```java
public class YourCustomClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {
    public YourCustomClassLoader(URL[] urls, ClassLoader parent) {
        super(urls, parent);
    }

    @Override
    protected Class&lt;?&gt; loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {
        // Check if the class should be loaded by the parent ClassLoader
        if (name.startsWith(&quot;com.mysql&quot;) || name.startsWith(&quot;org.mysql&quot;)) {
            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);
        }

        // try to load the class using your custom ClassLoader
        try {
            Class&lt;?&gt; clazz = findClass(name);
            if (resolve) {
                resolveClass(clazz);
            }
            return clazz;
        } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
            // If the class not found in this ClassLoader, delegate to parent ClassLoader as fallback
            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);
        }
    }

    @Override
    protected Class&lt;?&gt; findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {
        // Extract class source file from JAR and load it
        byte[] classBytes = extractClassBytesFromJar(name);
        return defineClass(name, classBytes, 0, classBytes.length);
    }
}

``` 

Then you can use a custom `getLoader()` method, to get the custom class loader:

```java
private CustomClassLoader getLoader() throws MalformedURLException {
    ClassLoader parent = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();
    File file = new File(&quot;to_jar_file&quot;);
    URL[] urls = new URL[]{file.toURI().toURL()};
    return new YourCustomClassLoader(urls, parent);
}
```

For extracting a class from a jar (the implementation of this method `extractClassBytesFromJar`) you cloud have a look at `java.util.jar.JarFile` or a third-party library like [Apache Commons Compress][1] or the Java Archive (JAR) API.


  [1]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-compress/

